   BOARD MEMBERS

   KATHLEEN CONNELL
   CALIFORNIA CONTROLLER AND BOARD MEMBER
   Kathleen Connell was elected California's Controller in 1994, bringing
   with her a strong background in business, education, and finance. In
   1998 she was re-elected. In addition to serving as a member of the
   California Victim Compensation and Government Claims Board, Controller
   Connell is a member of more than 50 policy-making boards and
   commissions.
   Prior to being elected Controller, Controller Connell ran her own
   investment banking firm and served as vice president and director for
   Chemical Bank of New York. She also served as Director of Housing for
   the City of Los Angeles.
   Controller Connell has a Ph.D. from UCLA, taught graduate level courses
   at the UCLA and UC Berkeley business schools, and was founder and
   director of the Center for Finance and Real Estate at the UCLA School
   of Management.
   In addition to her academic credentials, Controller Connell holds six
   securities licenses from the Securities and Exchange Commission.

